<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Quick Text translation</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Quick Text lets you translate short pieces of text instantly without uploading a file.
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to Quick Text</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      From the sidebar under Document Translation, click <strong>Quick Text</strong>.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Type or paste some text</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Try a common council communication, for example:
    </p>
    <div class="govuk-inset-text">
      "Your bin collection day is changing. From next Monday, your recycling will be collected on Wednesday instead of Thursday. Please put your bin out by 7am."
    </div>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Select a target language</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Choose from 75+ languages. Try some common community languages:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Welsh (cy)</strong> - for councils with bilingual obligations</li>
      <li><strong>Polish (pl)</strong> - one of the most spoken community languages</li>
      <li><strong>Urdu (ur)</strong> - widely spoken across UK councils</li>
      <li><strong>Bengali (bn)</strong> - important for many London boroughs</li>
      <li><strong>Arabic (ar)</strong> - right-to-left language support</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>View the translation</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The translation appears instantly. You'll see the original English text alongside the
      translated version.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

